    "## Introduction"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Car accidents cause enormous amounts of injuries and fatalities around the world. Road Speeds are usually decided on based on the type of road i.e highway/number of bends/minor or major road etc. If there is a legal speed limit put in place on a road, the likelihood is that most drivers will strive to adhere to this. \n",
    "However, what is those who adhere to the speed limit, cause the same number of accidents than those who don't? \n",
    "Should Speed limits on roads not be revised as a result of this?\n",
    "If weather conditions are altered, and this impacts on accident severity, should speed limit decisions be made based on this too?\n",
    "This project aims to determine from the data, whether speeding is a significant causal factor in accident fatalities and if so, whether more strict measure should be put in place to punish those who do speed."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The data being used is a shared dataset from Seattle city, it shows a record of the occurrence of traffic accidents from 2004 to the present day. This data was provided as a sample dataset for the purpose of the course completion and it was given as an option to use or not.\n",
    "I opted to use this dataset simply for its size. It is in the researchers best interest to use a representative sample for the purpose of research accuracy. \n",
    "More specifically, the data in use will take the variables road conditions and speeding and examine their significance to accident severity.\n"
   ]
