    "## Methodology"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Our predictor variable will be accident severity and our independent variables will be weather conditions and speed.\n",
    "We must prepare the dataset first through normalizing and changing the nature of the variables in use.\n",
    "The outcome variable was transformed so that it either predicted the presence of injury = 2 or no injury = 1. Fatality was categorised under injury for the purpose of convenience. The road conditions vaiable was transformed to be categorical as opposed to string for the purpose of the analysis and the labelling of speeding was transformed to show 1 as the pressence of speeding while 0 indicated the absense.\n",
    "Preliminary analysis led to the elimination missing values and changed outcome variable type to integer.\n",
    "The data was \n",
    "Due to the dataset size and in order to work with the dataset as cleanly as possible, the data was transformed and only the variables in use were uploaded to the workbook.\n",
    "It was decided that Logistic Regression analysis will be used to determine future impact of speeding and weather conditions on accident severity.The logistic regression model in use was decided as the outcome variable in question is categorical. \n",
    "The logistic regression model was then evaluated by calculating Logloss and JAccard index.\n"
   ]
  },
